RulesName: Add suffix s-Plural for Countable nouns

Comment: The past participle is generally identical to the past tense form (I have studied, lived, lifted, etc.), but many verbs have suppletive past participles (e.g., I have eaten, sung, written, etc.).

RulesName: Change sh+s[Third Singular Present] to sh+es
When verb stem ends with CVC, reduplicate final C before adding -ed
Comment: committed, controlled, dipped, dropped, grabbed, hugged, planned, plotted, regretted, stopped, tripped, whipped, wrapped   There are exceptions: delivered, entered, gathered, honored    This rule shouldn't apply when the final consonant is r as in covered; we don't want coverred.

RulesName: When verb stem ends with CVC, reduplicate final C before adding -ing
When verb stem ends with e,  delete the -e before adding -ed
When Verb stem ends with -e, delete the -e before adding -ing
When an Adjective stem ends with CVC, reduplicate the final C before adding -er
When an Adjective stem ends with CVC, reduplicate the final C before adding -est
Change final y to i before adding -ed
Change y+s[Third Singular Present] to i+es
Select the Stem form for Mass nouns
Comment: Mass nouns don't have a plural form, so we use the stem.  wheat, peace, sand, etc.
more carefully, more completely, more easily
most carefully, most completely, most easily

RulesName: Change final y to i before -ed
Comment: studied   We don't want this rule to apply when the y is preceded by a vowel (e.g., annoyed).
